  "texts": [
    "(p.6).For this research, the phenomenon of DeFi is purposely treated as a paradigm, as it is the widest form of consensus within a science, yet it sets apart one scientific group from another.",
    "Simultaneously, a paradigm incorporates, defines, and connects models, theories, methods, and tools that exist within its domain [24].",
    "However, even when using this rather large common denominator, another obstacle emerges before a unifying definition can be provided when looking at the above-mentioned definitions of DeFi: As varied as the objects that describe the term DeFi are the characteristics ascribed to them.",
    "They include attributes such as \"decentral\" [2, p.173], \"decentralized\" and \"disintermediated\", [18, p.121], \"transparent and interoperable\" [21, p.503], and \"public and unreliable\" [22, p.102].",
    "This further underscores the need for a sound taxonomy delineating the characteristics of DeFi, the business models it enables, and the risks it entails."
